  "prompt": "What is the nicest library at Columbia to work at?",
  "response": "Columbia University has several libraries, each offering a unique environment for studying and working. Many students consider the **Butler Library** to be one of the nicest due to its spacious reading areas, extensive collections, and iconic architecture. It provides a mix of quiet study spaces and group study areas, making it versatile for different working styles.\n\nThe **Rare Book & Manuscript Library** is also notable for its stunning reading room and unique collections, although it may not be ideal for all-day studying since it's more specialized. \n\nOther options like the **Health Sciences Library** and the **Avery Architectural and Fine Arts Library** also provide excellent resources and environments tailored to specific fields.\n\nUltimately, the best library can depend on your personal preferences, such as the type of work you're doing and the kind of atmosphere you thrive in.",
